---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContactCTA from '../../components/ContactCTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="HBO — Jason Ferrara" transparentNav>
  <article class="case-study">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container hero-centered">
        <img src="/images/hbo/HBO_logo.svg" alt="HBO" class="hero-logo animate" />
        <h1 class="animate" style="--delay: 0.1s">Scaling HBO's Transition to Streaming</h1>
        <div class="hero-meta animate" style="--delay: 0.15s">
          <span class="meta-detail">UX Design Manager</span>
          <span class="meta-sep">/</span>
          <span class="meta-detail">2013&ndash;2019</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-visual animate" style="--delay: 0.25s">
          <img src="/images/hbo/hbo_devices_og.png" alt="HBO NOW; cross-device experience" class="hero-device-img" />
        </div>
        <div class="hero-body">
          <p class="animate" style="--delay: 0.3s">HBO was undergoing a fundamental shift from premium cable network to direct-to-consumer streaming platform. The organization was evolving from linear programming to on-demand digital experiences across web, mobile, and connected TV ecosystems.</p>
          <p class="animate" style="--delay: 0.35s">I led a team of five designers responsible for content discovery and playback experiences during the launch and expansion of HBO NOW, helping establish the cross-device foundations that later evolved into HBO Max. This work required not only experience design across 20+ device ecosystems, but the maturation of design standards, delivery models, and cross-functional alignment during a period of rapid platform growth.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Cross-Device Platform Scale -->
    <section class="cs-section cs-section-alt container">
      <div class="section-top-copy">
        <span class="cs-label animate">Evolving Beyond Linear Cable</span>
        <h2 class="cs-heading animate" style="--delay: 0.1s">Establishing the Streaming Foundation</h2>
        <p class="cs-intro animate" style="--delay: 0.15s">Streaming required rethinking how audiences discover and engage with content across devices, creating a unified system that supported both editorial storytelling and scalable platform growth.</p>
        <p class="cs-intro cs-intro-secondary animate" style="--delay: 0.2s">I led the creation of shared architectural principles and cross-device UX standards that reduced fragmentation and created a consistent HBO experience across web, native mobile, and connected TV.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="impact-grid impact-grid-3col">
        <div class="impact-metric animate">
          <span class="impact-delta">20+</span>
          <span class="impact-label">Device Ecosystems Supported</span>
        </div>
        <div class="impact-metric animate" style="--delay: 0.1s">
          <span class="impact-delta">2</span>
          <span class="impact-label">Webby Awards</span>
        </div>
        <div class="impact-metric animate" style="--delay: 0.2s">
          <span class="impact-delta">5</span>
          <span class="impact-label">Designers Led at Peak</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <span class="cs-sublabel animate">Notable Work</span>

      <div class="feature feature-full animate">
        <div class="feature-full-inner">
          <div class="feature-image">
            <img src="/images/hbo/hbo_devices.png" alt="HBO cross-device experience" />
          </div>
          <div class="feature-full-copy">
            <h3>Cross-Device Experience Architecture</h3>
            <p>Defined scalable navigation and content discovery frameworks that adapted across desktop, native mobile, and connected TV environments. Established shared patterns and governance practices that reduced fragmentation while respecting platform-specific interaction models.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature animate">
          <div class="feature-image">
            <img src="/images/hbo/hbo-surf-hero.png" alt="HBO streaming discovery experience" />
          </div>
          <h3>Streaming Discovery and Playback Evolution</h3>
          <p>Led the design of core discovery and playback experiences supporting the shift from linear browsing to on-demand streaming. Balanced editorial storytelling with usability, performance constraints, and subscription conversion pathways across devices.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature animate" style="--delay: 0.1s">
          <div class="feature-image">
            <img src="/images/hbo/hbo_tvos.png" alt="HBO on Apple tvOS" />
          </div>
          <h3>Apple tvOS Launch Partnership</h3>
          <p>Led design efforts for HBO as a launch partner during Apple's introduction of tvOS, bringing the streaming experience to a new connected TV platform at its inception. Navigated evolving platform standards, certification requirements, and hardware constraints while ensuring HBO's content discovery and playback experience remained cohesive and premium.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature animate" style="--delay: 0.2s">
          <div class="feature-image">
            <img src="/images/hbo/VNT.png" alt="HBO interactive editorial experience with VICE" />
          </div>
          <h3>Interactive Editorial Experiences with VICE</h3>
          <p>Partnered with VICE to design interactive content experiences that extended HBO's storytelling beyond traditional streaming formats. These initiatives blended editorial narrative with digital interaction, introducing immersive features that encouraged deeper engagement and experimentation within HBO's digital ecosystem.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <ContactCTA variant="case-study" />

  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style is:global>
  html {
    background: #f7f5f2 !important;
  }
</style>

<style>
  /* Page Gradient */
  .case-study {
    position: relative;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #d9dce6 0%, #edeef3 35%, #f0eee9 65%, #f7f5f2 100%);
  }

  .case-study::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: -100vh;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 100vh;
    background: #d9dce6;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding: 4.5rem 0 5rem;
    padding-top: calc(4.5rem + var(--nav-height));
  }

  .hero-centered {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-logo {
    height: 35px;
    width: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    display: block;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .hero-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
  }

  .meta-detail {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .meta-sep {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-border);
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  /* Hero Visual */
  .hero-visual {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .hero-device-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .hero-body {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .hero-body p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* Section */
  .cs-section {
    padding-top: 5rem;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .cs-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cs-heading {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .cs-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .cs-intro-secondary {
    margin-top: -2.5rem;
  }

  .cs-section-alt {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* Side-by-side intro + metrics */
  .section-top-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .section-top-copy {
    max-width: 66%;
  }

  .section-top-copy .cs-intro {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .section-top-copy .cs-intro + .cs-intro {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .impact-grid-side {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 2.5rem 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.75rem;
    padding-left: 4rem;
    border-left: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .cs-sublabel {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* Feature Full-Width */
  .feature-full {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .feature-full-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .feature-full .feature-image {
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
  }

  .feature-full .feature-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    object-fit: contain;
  }

  /* Features Grid */
  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .feature-image {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
  }

  .feature-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    object-fit: contain;
  }

  .feature h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .feature p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  /* Impact */
  .impact-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    gap: 3.5rem 4rem;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .impact-grid-3col {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }

  .impact-metric {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .impact-delta {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 4.8vw, 3.6rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .impact-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .section-top-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }

    .impact-grid-side {
      padding-left: 0;
      border-left: none;
    }

    .feature-full-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .features-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .impact-grid {
      gap: 2.5rem 2rem;
    }

    .impact-grid-3col {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
